description: Describes all trace types with their properties.
name: Hansken Trace Model

id.description: Unique identifier of the trace within an image.

image.description: Unique identifier of the trace's image.

modelVersion.description: Version of the model used for the trace.

parent.description: Unique identifier of the parent trace.

pathItems.description: The individual items that make up the path property.

path.description: The logical path where the trace is located on the image, including the name of the trace itself.

previews.description: Map of previews by mime type.

siblingId.description: Unique identifier of the trace among its siblings.

origins.description: Designates where the trace was produced ("what was the origin of this trace"). Origins support all categories.

system.description: Categories added by the extraction system

user.description: Categories added manually by a user

privileged.description: Whether the trace has privileged access: suspected, confirmed or rejected.

tags.description: User defined tags for this trace.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the note was created.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which the note was last modified.

text.description: The body text of the note.

user.description: The user who created the note.

accessedOn.description: The date and time of the last usage of the account.

active.description: Can the user account be used or is the account disabled or locked.

application.description: The application using the account.

createdOn.description: The date and time of account creation.

expiresOn.description: The date and time of expiration of the account.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time of the last modification of the account.

name.description: The account login name or another identifier that describes the account e.g. email address.

password.description: The stored password, might be encrypted.

passwordType.description: The type of password, for instance plain-text or encrypted.

timestamps.description: Additional timestamps found for account e.g. timestamps.firstUsedOn.

type.description: The type of account, for instance OS, website, email.

misc.description: Additional information about the account archive.

address.description: A physical location in the world.

application.description: The application using the address.

type.description: The type of the address, for instance home or work.

application.description: The application for which this trace is an addressbook.

misc.description: Additional information about the address book.

application.description: A software application.

id.description: The unique identifier of the application.

installedOn.description: The installation date of the application.

package.description: The package of the application, e.g. com.example.ExampleMessenger.

permissions.description: The permissions requested by the application.

purchasedOn.description: The purchase date of the application.

version.description: The registered version of the application.

misc.description: Additional information about the application archive.

application.description: The name of the application from which the attachment originates.

encoding.description: The encoding that is used for sending the attachment, e.g. BASE64, BITS_7.

type.description: The type of attachment.

audio.description: A media trace that contains audio.

bitrate.description: The bitrate of the audio in bits per second.

duration.description: The duration of the audio in seconds.

format.description: The format of the audio. For example: mp3 or flac.

metadata.description: Audio metadata, e.g. title, genre, artist.

bookmark.description: A bookmark to a web pages or files using a web browser.

accessedOn.description: The date and time at which the web page or file was last opened.

application.description: The name of the web browser from which the bookmarks originates.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which this bookmark was created.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which this bookmark was last modified.

visitCount.description: The minimal number of times this bookmark has been visited by this web browser.

bookmarkArchive.description: A list of bookmarks to web pages and files using a web browser.

application.description: The name of the web browser from which the bookmarks originates.

browserHistory.description: Information on a web page or file that has been visited with a web browser.

accessedOn.description: The date and time at which the web page or file was last visited.

application.description: The name of the web browser that was used to visit the web page or file.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which this log entry was created.

misc.description: Additional information on this browser history.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which this visited web page or file was last modified. This timestamp is provided by the web site's server.

pageTitle.description: The title of the visited web page or file.

type.description: The type of page or file that has been visited, typically this property has value "URL".

url.description: The address of the visited web page or file.

user.description: The user that visited this web page or file.

visitCount.description: The minimal number of times this web page or file has been visited by this web browser.

browserHistoryLog.description: Log containing the history of visited web pages and files with a web browser.

application.description: The name of the web browser from which the log originates.

calendar.description: A collection of appointments and meetings.

application.description: The application for which this a calendar.

calendarEntry.description: An entry in a calendar, for instance an appointment or a meeting.

application.description: The application for which this a calendar entry.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the calendar entry was created.

endsOn.description: The date and time at which the event ends.

importance.description: The importance of the calendar entry.

misc.description: Additional information on the calendar entry.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which the calendar entry was last modified.

owner.description: The organizer of the calendar event.

private.description: Is the event marked as private?

remindOn.description: The date and time at which a reminder is given about the calendar entry.

startsOn.description: The date and time at which the event starts.

status.description: The status of the event, for instance accepted, pending or cancelled.

type.description: A free format text identifier, used for identifying type of calendar entry, for instance meeting or event.

carved.description: A carved trace is not available in the file system, but is found in the (unallocated) binary data in the image.

partial.description: Partial is set to true if the carved trace is only partially recovered.

beginsOn.description: The certificate is not valid before this date.

expiresOn.description: The certificate is not valid after this date.

serialNumber.description: The serial number of the certificate.

chatConversation.description: A set of messages from one chat conversation.

administrators.description: A list of administrators in this chat conversation.

application.description: The application for which this is a chat conversation, e.g. "Skype" or "MSN".

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the conversation was created.

misc.description: Additional information about the chat conversation.

participants.description: A list of members in this chat conversation.

sessionId.description: An unique identifier for the chat conversation, corresponding with the sessionId of underlying chat events.

subject.description: The subject of the chat conversation.

chatEvent.description: Log containing a chat event, e.g. the transfer of a file or the opening of a webcam session.

application.description: The application for which this is a log file, e.g. "Skype" or "MSN".

messageId.description: An identifier for the chat event.

misc.description: Additional information about the chat event.

sentOn.description: The time at which the chat entry was sent.

sessionId.description: An identifier for the chat session in which the chat log entry took place.

timestamps.description: Additional timestamps for the chat event.

type.description: The type of chat log entry, e.g. invitation, join, leave.

application.description: The application for which this is a log file, e.g. "Skype" or "MSN".

chatMessage.description: A single message sent in a chat.

application.description: The application for which this is a chat message, e.g. "Skype" or "MSN".

deliveredOn.description: The time at which the chat message was delivered.

messageId.description: An identifier for the chat message.

misc.description: Additional information about the chat message.

readOn.description: The time at which the chat message was read.

sentOn.description: The time at which the chat message was sent.

sessionId.description: An identifier for the chat session from which the chat message originates.

timestamps.description: Additional timestamps for the chat message.

algorithm.description: The algorithm used to compress the trace.

compressedSize.description: The number of bytes of the compressed data.

compressionRatio.description: The compression ratio of the compressed data.

modifiedOn.description: The last time the compressed content was changed.

originalName.description: The name of the original file.

originalOperatingSystem.description: The original operating system that created the file.

accessedOn.description: The time the connection was last accessed.

createdOn.description: The time the connection was initiated for the first time.

expiresOn.description: The time the connection is going to expire.

type.description: The type of the connection.

misc.description: Additional information about the connection archive.

contact.description: Contact found in an application, for example an entry in an address book.

application.description: The application for which this contact is used, for example Skype or MSN.

emailAddresses.description: The email addresses of the contact.

firstName.description: The first name of the contact.

lastName.description: The last name of the contact.

middleName.description: The middle name of the contact.

name.description: The name of the contact (firstName + lastName).

phoneNumbers.description: The phone numbers of the contact.

screenName.description: The display name of the contact.

timestamps.description: Timestamps that relate to the contact.

type.description: The type of the contact, for example friend, work.

cookie.description: A piece of data used by a (remote) web page, stored on the local machine.

accessedOn.description: The last time at which the cookie was accessed.

application.description: The name/identifier of the web browser from which cookies is extracted.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the cookie was created.

domain.description: The domain for which the cookie is stored, for example nfi.minjus.nl.

expiresOn.description: The expiration time of the cookie.

path.description: String representation of the path of the cookie.

secure.description: If the cookie is secure it cannot be delivered over an unencrypted session such as http.

application.description: The application for which this trace is a cookieArchive for example FireFox or IE.

algorithm.description: The algorithm for which the key is used.

base64.description: The contents of the key represented as base64.

createdOn.description: The date this key is created.

encoded.description: The contents of the key encoded in the given format.

format.description: The format used to encode the key.

hasPrivate.description: Whether the key contains a private key.

isMaster.description: Whether the key is a master key.

type.description: The type of key, for example private, public or secret.

userIds.description: The user IDs associated with the key.

cryptoKeyPair.description: Two crypto keys of types public and private.

application.description: The name of the application used for this key pair.

cryptocurrencyWallet.description: A collection of crypto keys and contacts of a cryptocurrency wallet.

misc.description: Additional information about the cryptocurrency wallet.

type.description: The type of the cryptocurrency wallet, for example Bitcoin, Litecoin or Ethereum.

data.description: The data (content) of the trace, indexed by data type. For example data.raw.size, data.text.size

descriptor.description: An opaque reference to the actual bytes that make up the data.

entropy.description: Shannon entropy (a measure of randomness) of the data.

fileType.description: File type of the data. For example 'Adobe Pdf'.

hash.description: Hash values of the data, keyed by algorithm. For example: hash.md5='d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e', hash.sha1='da39a3ee5e6b4b0d3255bfef95601890afd80709'

hashHitInfo.description: Information about a hash hit. For example: hashHitInfo.nsrl.os='Windows'

hashHits.description: A list of hash sets that contain a hash of this trace.

hashMisses.description: A list of hash sets that do NOT contain a hash of this trace.

imageOffset.description: The offset at which the start of data can be found, relative to the start of the image data.

mimeClass.description: MIME type derived classification of the data. For example 'audio', 'document', 'picture', or 'text'.

mimeType.description: MIME type of the data. For example 'text/html' or 'audio/mp3'.

parentOffset.description: The offset at which the start of data can be found, relative to the start of the parent trace's data.

size.description: The size of the data in bytes.

type.description: The type of data, contains the key: raw, text, plain...

deleted.description: A trace that has been deleted from the file system, or has been placed in a recycle bin or trash can.

deletedOn.description: The deletion time of the trace.

misc.description: Additional information about the deleted trace.

originalName.description: The name of the trace before it was deleted.

originalPath.description: The path of the trace before it was deleted.

originalSize.description: The size of the trace before it was deleted.

dns.description: IP DNS information regardless of lookup or reverselookup

ip.description: An ip address in dotted notation or semicolon notation for IPv6.

misc.description: Additional information about the DNS information.

document.description: A document, for example an Office documents.

application.description: The name of the application used to author the file.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the document was created.

lastAuthor.description: The last author that updated the document.

lastPrintedOn.description: The time at which the document was last printed.

lastSavedOn.description: The time at which the document was last saved.

misc.description: Additional information about the document, e.g. keywords, comments and revisions.

pageCount.description: The number of pages in the document.

type.description: The type of the document, e.g. document, spreadsheet or presentation.

application.description: The application storing this email.

bcc.description: A list of blank carbon copied receiver's email addresses.

cc.description: A list of carbon copied receiver's email addresses.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the email was created.

hasAttachment.description: Indicates if the email has an attachment.

headers.description: The email headers of the email.

inReplyTo.description: A unique identifier for identifying the email this email is a reply to.

messageId.description: A unique identifier for identifying the email.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the email and/or its read status was last modified.

read.description: Indicates if the email has been marked as read.

receivedOn.description: The time at which the email message was received.

references.description: A list of email message identifiers this email relates to.

sentOn.description: The time at which the email was sent.

to.description: A lists of receiver's email addresses.

emailArchive.description: An archive containing email folders and/or messages.

application.description: The application using this emailArchive.

misc.description: Additional information about the email archive.

name.description: The name of the email archive.

application.description: The application storing this email folder.

messageCount.description: The number of email messages in the email folder.

misc.description: Additional information about the email folder.

name.description: The name of the email folder.

unreadMessageCount.description: The number of unread email messages in the email folder.

encrypted.description: Data is recognized to be encrypted and can only be viewed with a cryptoKey or password.

algorithm.description: The algorithm used to encrypt the trace.

application.description: The name of the application used to encrypt the trace.

decrypted.description: True when the encrypted trace is decrypted, empty otherwise.

decryptionKey.description: A string representation of the key used to decrypt this trace, base64 encoded if needed.

decryptionKeySerialNumber.description: The serial number of the key used to decrypt this trace.

decryptionKeySerialNumbers.description: All serial numbers of the certificates of the keys that can decrypt this trace.

misc.description: Additional information about the encrypted trace.

event.description: An event, mainly used for operating system events.

action.description: The action taken in response to the event.

application.description: The application that generated the event.

category.description: The category of the event, a number or text to classify the event.

computerName.description: A name of the computer on which the log entry was created.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the event was created.

endedOn.description: The time at which the event ended.

generatedOn.description: The time at which the event was generated.

index.description: The index of the event in the event log.

misc.description: Additional information on the event log entry.

runCount.description: The number or times this event was run.

source.description: The source of the event, for example the name of the application that caused the event to occur.

startedOn.description: The time at which the event started.

text.description: The textual representation of the event.

type.description: The type of the event, for example "information", "warning" or "error".

user.description: The user for whom the event was created.

eventLog.description: Log containing events, amongst others from the operating system.

application.description: The application for which this is an event log.

misc.description: Additional information on the event log.

application.description: The name of the application used to author the file.

architecture.description: The architecture of the system this executable was compiled for.

compiledOn.description: The date and time at which the executable was compiled.

majorVersion.description: The major version of this executable.

minorVersion.description: The minor version of this executable.

subSystem.description: The subsystem the executable is built for.

file.description: A file is a block of arbitrary information, or resource for storing information.

accessedOn.description: The last time at which the file was accessed.

changedOn.description: The time at which the metadata of the file was last changed.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the file was created.

entryId.description: A unique identifier for the file within the filesystem. Currently, used for NTFS MFT entry id.

extension.description: The file name extension: everything after the last dot. Not present if the file has no dot in its name.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the content of the file was last modified.

path.description: The path of the file in the filesystem, including filename.

fileArchive.description: A collection of folders and files packed into one file.

misc.description: Additional information about the file archive.

type.description: The type of a file archive, e.g. ZIP, GZIP or RAR.

fileTransfer.description: A file transfer log entry contains the details of a file transfer that took place.

application.description: The application used for the file transfer., e.g. "FTP" or "MSN".

destinationPath.description: The destination for the file that is transferred.

finishedOn.description: The time at which the file transfer finished.

fromHost.description: The source address of the file transfer.

message.description: Additional message attached to the file transfer.

messageId.description: An identifier for the file transfer.

misc.description: Additional information on the file transfer.

sessionId.description: An identifier for the session in which the file transfer took place.

source.description: The source of the file that is transferred.

startedOn.description: The time at which the file transfer started.

timestamps.description: Additional timestamps for the file transfer.

toHosts.description: The destination addresses of the file transfer.

transferredOn.description: The time at which the file transfer took place (used when no explicit start and finished time is available).

type.description: The direction of the file transfer, e.g. send or receive.

fileTransferLog.description: A file transfer log contains the history of a file transfers.

application.description: The application used for the file transfer., e.g. "FTP" or "MSN".

misc.description: Additional information about the file transfer.

filesystem.description: A filesystem is a special-purpose database for the storage, organization, manipulation, and retrieval of data.

misc.description: Additional information on the filesystem, for example the version number.

type.description: The type of a filesystem, for example NTFS or FAT32.

folder.description: A folder is a container within a filesystem, in which groups of files and other folders can be kept and organized.

accessedOn.description: The last time at which the folder was accessed.

changedOn.description: The time at which the metadata of the folder was last changed.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the folder was created.

entryId.description: A unique identifier for the folder within the filesystem. Currently, used for NTFS MFT entry id.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the content of the folder was last modified.

path.description: The path of the folder in the filesystem.

gps.description: A GPS location, a possibly timed global position.

application.description: The application which stores the GPS entry.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the GPS entry was created.

hdop.description: The horizontal dilution of precision of the GPS location.

latlong.description: The latitude and longitude of the GPS location in decimal degrees.

misc.description: Additional information about the GPS location.

pdop.description: The positional (3D) dilution of precision of the GPS location.

tdop.description: The temporal dilution of precision of the GPS location.

vdop.description: The vertical dilution of precision of the GPS location.

gpsLog.description: A log containing tracks and/or gps entries.

application.description: The application for which this is a log file, e.g. "Tom Tom Go 6100".

createdOn.description: The date/time this gpsLog was created.

description.description: A free text description of the gpsLog.

identity.description: An identity is a small contact card that describes identifiers used elsewhere in the trace.

emailAddress.description: The email address of the identity.

firstName.description: The first name of the identity.

id.description: The unique identifier of the identity, for example an email address, username or phone number.

lastName.description: The last name of the identity.

ldapDn.description: The ldap distinguished names of the identity.

originalValue.description: The original value from which identity properties were extracted, e.g. "John Doe <john@doe.com>".

phoneNumber.description: The phone number of the identity.

screenName.description: The display name of the identity.

status.description: The social status of the identity , e.g. "being happy", "at the gym", ... .

uuid.description: The universal unique id of the identity.

image.description: An image is an artifact, that has a similar appearance to some subject - usually a physical object.

description.description: A free text description of the image.

type.description: The type of the image, e.g. EnCase, RAW or LocalFolder.

intercept.description: The result of a lawful intercept warrant

imei.description: The International Mobile Station Equipment Identity (IMEI) of the device involved in the intercept.

imsi.description: The International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI) of the Subscriber Identity Module (SIM) card involved in the intercept.

msisdn.description: The telephone number of the subscriber (MSISDN : Mobile Station International Subscriber Directory Number) involved in the intercept.

type.description: The original type of intercept used.

azimuth.description: Orientation of the main antenna beam

ecgi.description: The 'E-UTRAN Cell Global Identity' (E-CGI). This parameter is only applicable to the CS traffic cases where the available location information is the one received from the Mobility Management Entity (MME).

misc.description: Additional information about the intercept location.

observedOn.description: The date/time this location was observed.

rai.description: The Routeing Area Identifier (RAI) in the current Serving GPRS Support Node (SGSN).

tai.description: The Tracking Area Identity. This parameter is only applicable to the CS traffic where the available location information is the one received from the Mobility Management Entity (MME).

destinationIp.description: The destination ip address in dotted notation or semicolon notation for IPv6.

destinationPort.description: The destination port for a UDP or TCP connection.

ipProtocol.description: IP protocol by name like tcp, udp or number for unknown protocols.

sourceIp.description: The source ip address in dotted notation or semicolon notation for IPv6.

sourcePort.description: The source port for a UDP or TCP connection.

link.description: A link (or shortcut) is a trace that links to another trace.

accessedOn.description: The last time at which the link (shortcut) was accessed.

arguments.description: The arguments that are passed to the trace that is linked.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the link was created.

description.description: A free text description of the link.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the link was last modified.

target.description: The URI, file or folder that is linked.

targetFileLength.description: The length of the trace that is linked.

type.description: The type of the link.

visitCount.description: The minimal number of times this link has been visited.

volumeLabel.description: The label of the volume that is linked to.

volumeSerial.description: The serial number of the volume that is linked to.

volumeType.description: The type of the volume that is linked to.

workingDirectory.description: The name of the directory in which the target of the link must be executed.

memory.description: A piece of data in memory.

address.description: The address in memory of the trace.

misc.description: Additional information about the memory trace.

memoryImage.description: An image of a memory dump.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the memory image was created.

name.description: The name of the memory trace.

physicalAddressExtension.description: Indicates if the memory image uses physical address extension (PAE).

application.description: The application storing the note.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the note was created.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which the note was last modified.

application.description: The application storing the notes.

misc.description: Additional information about the note archive.

name.description: The name of the notes archive.

application.description: The application which stores the note folder.

misc.description: Additional information about the note archive.

name.description: The name of the notes folder.

application.description: The application which received or made the phone call, for example "Skype".

duration.description: The duration of the phone call in seconds.

endsOn.description: The date and time at which the phone call was terminated.

from.description: The phone number of the initiating party.

index.description: The index of the phone call in phone calls list.

misc.description: Additional information on the phone call.

startsOn.description: The date and time at which the phone call was initiated.

timestamps.description: Additional timestamps for a phone call.

type.description: The type of a phone call,for example incoming, outgoing, missed.

application.description: The application receiving or making the phone calls contained in this log.

picture.description: A picture is a two-dimensional visual representation.

application.description: The application storing the pictures.

aspectRatio.description: The aspect ratio of the picture, <1.0 indicating portrait orientation >1.0 indicating landscape orientation.

camera.description: The name/make of the camera that was used for taking the picture.

digitizedOn.description: The time at which the picture was digitized.

exif.description: The EXIF (Exchangeable Image File Format) information of the picture; the metadata contained in the picture.

format.description: The format of a picture, for example jpg or png.

height.description: The height of the picture in pixels.

index.description: The index of the picture in the container.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the content of the picture was modified.

originalTakenOn.description: The time at which the picture was originally taken.

photoDnaHash.description: The PhotoDNA Robust Hash of the picture.

photoDnaVector.description: The PhotoDNA Robust Hash of the picture, encoded as a vector.

type.description: The type of a picture, for example a thumbnail.

width.description: The width of the picture in pixels.

process.description: A process that runs (or exited) at the moment that the memory dump was created.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the process was created.

exitStatus.description: A small number passed from the process to the parent process when it has finished executing. In general, 0 indicates successful termination, any other number indicates a failure.

exitedOn.description: The time at which the process exited.

memoryAddress.description: The address (in memory) of the process.

parentId.description: The identifier of the process that created this process.

status.description: The status of the process, for example active or exited.

user.description: The user that owns the process.

registry.description: A registry hive contains configuration of a Microsoft Windows operating systems.

type.description: The type of a registry hive.

registryEntry.description: A registry entry is a configuration of a Microsoft Windows operating systems.

className.description: The value of a hidden attribute of the registry key often referred to as class name.

key.description: The flattend path, separated by slashes, of the entry in the registry hyve.

modifiedOn.description: The time at which the content of the registry key was last modified.

name.description: The name of the registry key.

type.description: The data type of the registry value.

value.description: The registry value is the optional value stored with the key.

signed.description: Data signed with a private key.

misc.description: Additional information on the signed data.

serialNumbers.description: Serial numbers of the signer certificates.

type.description: The type of the signed data.

task.description: An entry on a to-do list.

application.description: The application storing this task.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the task was created.

endsOn.description: The date and time at which the task ends.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which the task was last modified.

remindOn.description: The date and time at which a reminder is given about the calendar entry.

startsOn.description: The date and time at which the task starts.

status.description: The status of the event, for instance accepted, pending or cancelled.

type.description: The type of task to be performed.

application.description: The application storing this task list.

misc.description: Additional information about the to-do list.

owner.description: The owner of the to-do list.

application.description: The application sending or receiving this text message.

index.description: The index of the message in the text messages list.

misc.description: Additional information about the text message.

read.description: True if the text message has been read.

sentOn.description: The time at which the text message was sent.

type.description: the type of a text message, for example incoming, draft or outgoing.

application.description: The application sending or receiving text messages stored in this archive.

misc.description: Additional information about the text message archive.

name.description: The name of the text message archive.

messageCount.description: The number of text messages in the text message folder.

misc.description: Additional information about the text message folder.

name.description: The name of the text message folder.

unreadMessageCount.description: The number of unread text messages in the text message folder.

thumbnail.description: A miniature view of a picture.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the thumbnail was created.

modifiedOn.description: The date and time at which the thumbnail was modified.

type.description: The type of thumbnail.

application.description: The application maintaining the thumbnail archive.

misc.description: Additional information about the thumbnail archive.

track.description: A sequence of GPS locations marking a single track.

application.description: The application storing this track.

endsOn.description: The latest date and time of any gps location of the track.

startsOn.description: The earliest date and time of any gps location of the track.

unallocated.description: An unallocated trace is a part of an image that is not allocated to a physical trace.

path.description: The path where the unallocated space can be found in the filesystem.

fragment.description: Fragment pointing to a specific part in the resource.

fragments.description: Fragment split into its separate parts.

host.description: Domain name or IP address where the resource is located.

password.description: Password used to authenticate to this resource.

path.description: Path where the resource is located on the server.

port.description: Port on which communication takes place.

queries.description: Query split into its separate parts.

username.description: Username used to authenticate to this resource.

video.description: A media trace that contains video.

aspectRatio.description: The aspect ratio of the video, <1.0 indicating portrait orientation >1.0 indicating landscape orientation.

bitrate.description: The bitrate of the video in bits per second.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the video was created.

duration.description: The duration of the video in seconds.

format.description: The format of the video. For example: mp4.

framerate.description: The framerate of the video in frames per second.

height.description: The height the video in pixels.

metadata.description: Video metadata, e.g. title, genre, artist.

processedStream.description: Video stream index used for image processing.

streams.description: Stream type per index plus codec, for example audio: MP3 (MPEG audio layer 3), video: FLV / Sorenson Spark / Sorenson H.263 (Flash Video).

type.description: The type of video.

width.description: The width of the video in pixels.

volume.description: A volume is a single accessible storage area with a single file system.

description.description: A free text description of the volume.

id.description: The unique identifier of the volume.

sectorSize.description: The sector size of the volume.

classification.description: A statistical classification of a trace belonging to one or more classes / categories.

class.description: The class that the trace is classified as.

confidence.description: The classification confidence, expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.
The confidence value of the entity, between 0 and 1 inclusive.

encoding.description: The character encoding of the entity's raw value.

fvt.description: If present, indicates the index of the fvt (few-valued tracelet) from which the entity was extracted.

index.description: For properties that have a list of values, indicates from which value the entity was extracted. For example: email.to is a list of values; index=2 indicates that the entity was extracted from the second value

length.description: The raw, unnormalized length of the entity.

offset.description: The offset within the source property or data stream that the entity was found in.

source.description: The property or data stream that the entity was found in, e.g. email.to or data.raw.

type.description: The type of entity, e.g. emailAddress, iban, url, etc.

value.description: The normalized value of the entity.

prediction.description: A statistical prediction about a trace.

confidence.description: The prediction confidence, expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.

confidences.description: The prediction confidences, expressed as a numbers between 0.0 and 1.0.

count.description: A count for the given prediction.type.

modelName.description: Name of the model that produced this prediction.

modelVersion.description: Version of the model that produced this prediction.

offset.description: Offset from the start of this prediction.

offsets.description: Offsets from the start for the predictions, in seconds.

region.description: The prediction region as a polygon [x1, y1, x2, y2, ...] without wrapping back to start.

type.description: The type of the prediction, e.g. a classification, scene text or barcode.

search.description: Information related to a search query.

accessedOn.description: The time at which the search query was last performed.

misc.description: Additional information about the search query.

query.description: The query used to perform the search, containing for example the keyword.

source.description: The application or website used to perform the search query.

user.description: Name of the user that performed the search query.

createdOn.description: The date and time at which the trace was modified.

operation.description: How the trace properties were modified: added or removed.

user.description: The user who modified the trace.

valueNew.description: The new value of the audited property.

valueOld.description: The old value of the audited property.

origin.description: Information about the origin of the trace.

createdBy.description: Name of the tool that created the trace.

createdOn.description: Date and time when the trace was first created.

quality.description: Information about the quality of the value of a property.

aspect.description: Aspect of the value that has a quality concern. e.g. timezone, resolution, year

description.description: Description of the quality. e.g. using default timezone CET, 2 seconds, copied from parent file.modifiedOn

fvt.description: If present, indicates the index of the fvt (few-valued tracelet) which has a quality concern.

index.description: For properties that have a list of values, indicates which value which has a quality concern. It is 0 based. For example: connection.timestamps is a list of values; index=2 indicates the third value.

property.description: The name of the property. e.g. connection.timestamps.

toolrun.description: Information about the tools that were run to create this trace.

cause.description: In the event of tool failure, its cause message.

children.description: The number of fvt, mvt and traces created by the tool.

dataType.description: The data stream to which the tool was applied.

dataTypes.description: The data streams created by the tool.

duration.description: Duration of the tool's running time in seconds.

failureType.description: The type of failure: incidental, structural or environmental.

hanskenVersion.description: The version of hansken when this tool was run.

properties.description: The properties created by the tool.

result.description: The tool's result: success or failure.

startedOn.description: Date and time when the tool was started.

types.description: The types created by the tool.

collection.description: A trace can be part of a collection of traces, for example traces located in several places in the trace hierarchy that all belong to a single conversation.

type.description: The type of the collection; what this collection can be used for.

cryptoKeyInfo.description: A cryptoKey that is related to this trace.

property.description: The trace property where this key was referenced.

traceUid.description: The uid of the related trace.

userIds.description: The user IDs associated with the key.

traceUid.description: The uid of the referenced trace.

type.description: The type of the referenced trace, for example 'content' if the referenced trace contains the data of a fileTransfer.
